12.title: Calcium plus Vitamin D Supplementation and the Risk of Colorectal Cancer
12.text:
Randomized trial

Link: http://www.fp.ucalgary.ca/FMResidentSecure/Articles/Ca%20vit%20d%20and%20ca%20colon%20nejm%20feb%202006.pdf

From conclusions:

> "Daily supplementation of calcium with vitamin D for seven years had no effect on the incidence of colorectal cancer among postmenopausal women."

49.title: "Misleading conclusion. Thei..."
49.text: Misleading conclusion. Their 400 IU dose of Vit D was pathetically low and therefore totally ineffective. However if you look at table 2, you'll see that their data show that serum vit. D level was strongly inversely linked to colorectal cancer.
